  "instructions": [
    "heat the olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.",
    "add the chopped onion and sauté until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "add the minced garlic and cook for an additional 1-2 minutes.",
    "add the long-grain rice and stir to coat with oil and mix with onion and garlic.",
    "add the chicken broth, dried parsley, dried mint, lemon juice, apple cider vinegar, sea salt, and black pepper. Stir to combine.",
    "bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 18-20 minutes, or until the liquid has been absorbed and the rice is tender.",
    "remove from heat and let rest, covered, for 5 minutes.",
    "fluff the rice with a fork and serve hot."
